Uses of Package
Main.Consoles

Packages that use Main.Consoles
Package Description
Main.Consoles
This package holds the consoles of the game and their panels.
Main.MVC
This package holds the java files related to the MVC design pattern.
Main.Others
This package holds the other java classes which cannot be clearly fitted into another package.
  • Classes in Main.Consoles used by Main.Consoles
    Class Description
    CustomPanel
    Public class CustomPanel is used customise the levels based on the player choice such as level type, number of balls, number of rows of bricks, number of bricks in a row, number of brick types and brick types that spawn.
    DebugPanel
    Public class DebugPanel is used to call methods to reset ball count, reset ball and player position, move to previous or next level and set the ball movement speed.
  • Classes in Main.Consoles used by Main.MVC
    Class Description
    DebugConsole
    Public class DebugConsole is the container for the DebugPanel.
  • Classes in Main.Consoles used by Main.Others
    Class Description
    CustomConsole
    Public class CustomConsole is the container for the CustomPanel.
